org.pipseq.rdf.jena.filter

Class vote

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hp.hpl.jena.sparql.function.FunctionBase
      • org.pipseq.rdf.jena.filter.vote
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.hp.hpl.jena.sparql.function.Function

    public class vote
extends com.hp.hpl.jena.sparql.function.FunctionBase
    vote For use as a filter function within a SPARQL query. The vote function accepts a policy parameter followed by any number of "vote" or "ballot" parameters. The vote parameters are compared and a result is returned depending on agreement of the vote with the policy. If the policy is a resource with local name 'Unanimous', then all votes must agree. If the policy is a resource with local name 'Majority', then > 50% of all votes must agree. If the policy is a resource with local name 'SuperMajority', then > 66% of all votes must agree. Returns the agreed-upon vote or false.
